# Environment Variables

## Required Environment Variables

Copy this file to `.env.local` and fill in the required values:

```bash
# Database Configuration
DATABASE_URL=your_neon_database_url_here
POSTGRES_URL=your_postgres_url_here

# AI/ML Service Configuration  
CEREBRAS_API_KEY=your_cerebras_api_key_here

# Authentication (Clerk) - REQUIRED
NEXT_PUBLIC_CLERK_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=pk_test_your_publishable_key_here
CLERK_SECRET_KEY=sk_test_your_secret_key_here

# Clerk URLs (optional, use defaults if not specified)
NEXT_PUBLIC_CLERK_SIGN_IN_URL=/sign-in
NEXT_PUBLIC_CLERK_SIGN_UP_URL=/sign-up
NEXT_PUBLIC_CLERK_SIGN_IN_FALLBACK_REDIRECT_URL=/
NEXT_PUBLIC_CLERK_SIGN_UP_FALLBACK_REDIRECT_URL=/
```

## Getting API Keys

### Cerebras API Key
1. Sign up at https://cerebras.ai/
2. Navigate to API section in your dashboard
3. Generate a new API key
4. Add it to your `.env.local` file as `CEREBRAS_API_KEY=your_key_here`

### Clerk Authentication Keys (REQUIRED)
1. Sign up at https://clerk.com/
2. Create a new application
3. Go to API Keys section in your dashboard
4. Copy the "Publishable key" to `NEXT_PUBLIC_CLERK_PUBLISHABLE_KEY`
5. Copy the "Secret key" to `CLERK_SECRET_KEY`

### Database URLs
1. Set up your Neon database at https://neon.tech/
2. Copy the connection string to `DATABASE_URL` and `POSTGRES_URL`

## Security Notes
- Never commit `.env.local` or any `.env*` files to version control
- Keep your API keys secure and rotate them regularly
- Use different API keys for development and production environments
- Clerk keys starting with `pk_test_` and `sk_test_` are for development
- Use `pk_live_` and `sk_live_` keys in production